LONDON, June 23 (Reuters Breakingviews) - Investment banks like HSBC (HSBA.L) and Citigroup (C.N) are beefing up teams in the Middle East to rake in juicy IPO and M&A fees. In this Viewsroom podcast, Breakingviews columnists discuss why early investment is paying off. Also, the People’s Republic’s jobs crisis is likely to worsen. Listen to the podcast  Follow @aimeedonnellan on Twitter Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.